Bouygues, Gecina, GPE, Pizzorno, Vivendi: French Equity Preview

-- B y   H e l e n e   F o u q u e t
-- 
2011-05-17T04:00:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-16/bouygues-gecina-gpe-pizzorno-vivendi-french-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose stocks may have unusual changes in Paris. Symbols are in
parentheses after company names and prices are from the last
close.  France ’s CAC 40 Index fell 29.03, or 0.7 percent, to
3,989.82 in Paris. The SBF 120 Index retreated 0.7 percent to
3,006.25.  Bouygues SA (EN)  : The French building, television and
telecommunications company said first-quarter profit fell 81
percent, hurt by a lower contribution from its stake in Alstom
SA. The shares added 0.2 percent to 33.97 euros.  Gecina (GFC FP): The French property company plans to file
a public buyout offer for Gecimed’s shares, of which it owns at
98.6 percent stake, as it no longer considers it relevant to
keep the subsidiary as a listed entity. The shares were
unchanged at 100.05 euros.  GPE Groupe Pizzorno (GPE)  Environnement (GPE FP): The waste
treatment company said first-quarter sales rose 6.6 percent to
43.84 million euros. The shares retreated 1.2 percent to 18.92
euros.  Vivendi SA (VIV)  : The owner of the world’s largest music
and video-game companies said it signed a previously announced 5
billion-euro loan facility with 17 banks related to its purchase
of a 44 percent stake in French mobile phone operator SFR. The
shares fell 0.9 percent to 19.24 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
James Hertling in Paris at 
